# File: specs/feature-route-skill-tasks-through-skill-creator/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-route-skill-tasks-through-skill-creator/requirements.md
# Issue: #141

Feature: Route skill creation and update tasks through /skill-creator
  As a developer implementing or modifying a Claude Code skill definition through the SDLC pipeline
  I want write-code, spec-implementer, and verify-code to route skill-related work through /skill-creator
  So that all skill definitions meet Anthropic's official best practices regardless of how the task was initiated

  Background:
    Given the nmg-sdlc plugin is loaded
    And the SDLC pipeline is executing for a valid GitHub issue

  # --- Happy Path: Detection ---

  Scenario: Detect skill task by SKILL.md path suffix
    Given a task with file path "plugins/acme/skills/foo/SKILL.md"
    When the SKILL-TASK DETECTOR is applied
    Then the task is classified as skill-related

  Scenario: Detect skill task by description token
    Given a task whose description contains the phrase "Implement the foo skill"
    And the task file path does not end in SKILL.md
    When the SKILL-TASK DETECTOR is applied
    Then the task is classified as skill-related

  Scenario: Detect skill task by issue-title token
    Given the issue title contains the word "skill"
    And a task without SKILL.md in its path and without skill tokens in its description
    When the SKILL-TASK DETECTOR is applied
    Then the task is classified as skill-related

  # --- Happy Path: Routing With /skill-creator Available ---

  Scenario: write-code invokes /skill-creator for a detected task
    Given /skill-creator is installed
    And a skill task has been detected in write-code's task loop
    When write-code reaches that task
    Then /skill-creator is invoked with the task context and target file path
    And Write or Edit is NOT used to author the SKILL.md directly
    And the target SKILL.md exists at the declared path after execution

  Scenario: spec-implementer agent invokes /skill-creator for a detected task
    Given /skill-creator is installed
    And the spec-implementer agent is executing tasks sequentially
    And the next task has been detected as skill-related
    When the agent reaches that task
    Then /skill-creator is invoked for the task
    And the agent does NOT use Write or Edit to author the SKILL.md directly

  Scenario: verify-code routes a SKILL.md fix through /skill-creator
    Given /skill-creator is installed
    And verify-code has identified a finding in a file whose path ends in SKILL.md
    When verify-code applies the fix in Step 6a
    Then the fix is routed through /skill-creator with the finding context and existing file content
    And Write or Edit is NOT used to patch the SKILL.md directly
    And the fix appears in the verification report's Fixes Applied table with its routing noted

  # --- Graceful Degradation (Error Handling) ---

  Scenario: write-code emits verbatim warning when /skill-creator is missing
    Given /skill-creator is NOT installed
    And a skill task has been detected in write-code's task loop
    When write-code reaches that task
    Then the warning "skill-creator not available — implementing skill directly" is emitted in a fenced code block
    And write-code falls back to direct Write/Edit authoring
    And the pipeline completes without failure

  Scenario: spec-implementer emits verbatim warning when /skill-creator is missing
    Given /skill-creator is NOT installed
    And the spec-implementer agent encounters a detected skill task
    When the agent reaches that task
    Then the warning "skill-creator not available — implementing skill directly" is emitted in a fenced code block
    And the agent falls back to direct Write/Edit authoring
    And the agent completes execution without failure

  Scenario: verify-code emits verbatim warning when /skill-creator is missing
    Given /skill-creator is NOT installed
    And verify-code has identified a finding in a SKILL.md file
    When verify-code applies the fix in Step 6a
    Then the warning "skill-creator not available — implementing skill directly" is emitted in a fenced code block
    And the fix proceeds via direct Write/Edit
    And the verification report records the fix normally

  Scenario: Warning is emitted at most once per component run
    Given /skill-creator is NOT installed
    And a component processes multiple skill tasks in a single run
    When each skill task is processed
    Then the probe result is cached per run
    And the verbatim warning appears exactly once in the transcript for that run

  # --- Edge Cases ---

  Scenario: Conservative false-positive bias for ambiguous tasks
    Given /skill-creator is installed
    And a task has weak skill signals (e.g., only the issue body mentions "skill" while the task touches an unrelated file)
    When the SKILL-TASK DETECTOR is applied
    Then the task is classified as skill-related
    And /skill-creator is invoked (false-positive routing preferred over false-negative)
    And no warning about missing skill-creator is emitted

  Scenario: Non-skill task is unaffected
    Given a task with no SKILL.md in its file path
    And the task description contains no skill tokens
    And the issue title and body contain no skill tokens
    When the component executes the task
    Then the SKILL-CREATOR PROBE is NOT performed for this task
    And direct Write/Edit authoring is used as today
    And /skill-creator is NOT invoked

  Scenario: Unattended mode does not introduce interactive prompts
    Given the file .claude/unattended-mode exists at the project root
    And /skill-creator is installed
    And a skill task has been detected
    When the component routes the task through /skill-creator
    Then no AskUserQuestion prompt is raised by the routing logic
    And the probe remains a filesystem and system-reminder check only
    And execution proceeds without human intervention

  Scenario: Detection signals match case-insensitively at word boundaries
    Given a task whose description contains the word "Skills" (capitalized, plural)
    When the SKILL-TASK DETECTOR is applied
    Then the task is classified as skill-related

  Scenario: Detection does not false-match on substrings
    Given a task whose description contains the word "skillet" but no other skill signals
    And the file path does not end in SKILL.md
    And the issue does not contain the word "skill"
    When the SKILL-TASK DETECTOR is applied
    Then the task is NOT classified as skill-related

  # --- Data-Driven: Probe Availability Sources ---

  Scenario Outline: /skill-creator is considered available when any probe source matches
    Given a skill task has been detected
    And <probe_source> indicates /skill-creator is present
    When the SKILL-CREATOR PROBE runs
    Then /skill-creator is considered available
    And the component invokes /skill-creator instead of falling back

    Examples:
      | probe_source                                                 |
      | the user-skills directory (~/.claude/skills/skill-creator/)  |
      | a plugin-skills glob (~/.claude/plugins/**/skills/skill-creator/) |
      | the available-skills list in the current system reminder     |
